---
import FeaturesContainer from '@components/FeaturesContainer.astro';
import HeroContainer from '@components/HeroContainer.astro';
import IconBlock from '@components/IconBlock.astro';
import Prose from '@components/Prose.astro';
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout>
	<HeroContainer id='internship-overview'>
		<Fragment slot='heading'>
			<h2>Our summer internship is all about catching a Gospel Imaginary.</h2>
		</Fragment>
		<Fragment slot='body'>
			<p>
				We want to give you a taste of our shared convictions and help you think through further
				ministry training and partnership in Soutnern MN. <a href='#features'
					>Interested? Scroll down to learn more.</a
				>
			</p>
		</Fragment>
	</HeroContainer>

	<FeaturesContainer id='strategy' headingSide='left'>
		<Fragment slot='heading'>The Summer Internship is</Fragment>
		<Fragment slot='features'>
			<IconBlock title='Church-Hosted' icon='church'>
				A host church will provide the primary context for ministry practice as the intern is
				immersed in the normal ministry activity (elder meetings, member visits, Sunday School,
				small groups, membership classes, prayer gatherings, preaching, hospitality, etc.). Each
				intern will have a supervising pastor-mentor.
			</IconBlock>
			<IconBlock title='Cohort-Based' icon='church'>
				Interns will participate in a cohort spread throughout participating churches. The cohort
				will gather weekly for discussion and reflection on practical ministry topics as experienced
				in the local church setting. At scheduled times through the summer, the cohort will have
				extended training times together focused in four areas related to the TCT Southern Minnesota
				Vision: (1) Persuasive Preaching; (2) Intentional Ecclesiology; (3) Compelling Culture; and
				(4) Deliberately Rural Mission.
			</IconBlock>
			<IconBlock title='Church-Funded' icon='money'>
				The host church will be responsible to provide housing and a stipend of $4,800 for the
				twelve week internship. This position requires approximately twenty hours per week minimum.
				To maximize learning, interns are encouraged to participate in as local church ministry as
				possible.
			</IconBlock>
		</Fragment>
	</FeaturesContainer>

	<FeaturesContainer id='benefits' headingSide='right'>
		<Fragment slot='heading'>Five Reasons to Consider the Internship</Fragment>
		<Fragment slot='features'>
			<IconBlock title='Self-Assessment' icon='checkmark'>
				Through the internship experiences, the intern will assess their own desire and preparedness
				for pastoral ministry in general and for ministry in normative size and small place settings
				in particular.
			</IconBlock>
			<IconBlock title='Practical Training' icon='checkmark'>
				The intern will receive mentoring from a supervising pastor and cohort mentor. Through
				guided reading, discussion, and participation in essential areas of pastoral ministry, the
				intern will grow in competence in skills essential to ministry.
			</IconBlock>
			<IconBlock title='External Assessment and Affirmation' icon='checkmark'>
				The local church and supervising pastor will have the opportunity to assess (and
				Lord-willing, affirm) the intern’s gifts and calling to pastoral ministry.
			</IconBlock>
			<IconBlock title='Participation in the Life of a Healthy Church' icon='checkmark'>
				The intern will enjoy the loving support of a local church which assumes the responsibility
				for his care and training. Through participation in the weekly rhythms of the local church,
				the intern will enjoy the encouragement of other believers as he explores his calling.
			</IconBlock>
			<IconBlock title='Blessing to the Local Church' icon='checkmark'>
				The intern and the local church will have a mutually beneficial relationship. The intern
				will meet pastoral needs in the church and the church will be blessed as they exercise
				hospitable welcome to the intern.
			</IconBlock>
		</Fragment>
	</FeaturesContainer>
	<HeroContainer id='internship-overview'>
		<Fragment slot='heading'>
			<h2>To Apply</h2>
		</Fragment>
		<Fragment slot='body'>
			<p>
				Contact pastor Tyler Mykkanen at Sojourners Church (Albert Lea, MN) at
				<a href='tel:507-552-1595'>(507) 552-1595</a> or <a href='mailto:hello@smntct.org'
					>hello@smntct.org</a
				>.
			</p>
		</Fragment>
	</HeroContainer>
</BaseLayout>
